                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51/84: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schuyler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-13T20:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1921—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 14, 6:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>37. Your telegram number 23, August 11th, 5 p.m. The President has just received
                    cable from Keilhauer stating that he expects definite answer from the bankers
                    next Thursday<note n="2" xml:id="d819fn2">August 18.</note> and is unwilling to
                    extend time before then as the money urgently needed. He states that he has been
                    promised 3 million pesos payable on expiration of option on the same conditions.
                    Banker referred to recently told me he would lend nothing except on terms
                    approved by me. If the Keilhauer group will immediately agree to lend 3 million
                    on the terms of option the President will extend time for the remainder.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
